<br>
On a brave, if not too wise, solo foray I decided, one very late night, to venture into the Ssrae(whatchyamacallit) Temple in the Grey, for the very first time.  As I was waiting to zone in, I went ld and couldn't relog as I had a corrupted zone file.  Upon reinstalling the zone, I log in to find I'm at my bind point.  After petitioning to a GM, I'm told that the zone in question is subject to &quot;limited customer service&quot;...as limited as VI customer service is already.  Even after explaining that I went ld due to a bad zone file, the GM basically states to approach the situation in the spirit of adventure.  After a lot of running around (I had to get waterbreathing components as the Grey is devoid of air)...I zone back into the temple to find my corpse is nowhere to be seen.  As I later learned, somehow my LD character aggroed a mob and was summoned behind a door.  <br>
<br>
A quick survey of the zone-in area revealed that any further advance into the zone would require killing the various guards near the zone-in, as they appeared to see through invis.  I also learned very quickly, that they summon.  Now, clearly the quickest solution was to enlist the aid of a necromancer who could corpse summon.  But given that many necros are solo-oriented, I can honestly say that I'd never met a necro up to that point.  Long story short, it took a very long time to find a necro capable and able to perform the corpse summons, and all the while I'm thinking about my corpse poofing.<br>
<br>
That situation was stressful enough without the addition of being unable to search for a necromancer.  I'm sure others have experienced similar situations.<br>
<br>
If anyone wants to start a petition or run a poll to allowed even limited display of class/level information, I&quot;m all for it.<br>
